00:37:35.956 --> 00:37:39.216
To tell you a little bit about

00:37:39.266 --> 00:37:41.166
template images, in case you

00:37:41.166 --> 00:37:42.326
don't already know about them,

00:37:43.776 --> 00:37:45.116
it's important to understand

00:37:45.246 --> 00:37:47.296
that the transparency of each

00:37:47.296 --> 00:37:51.066
pixel is maintained, but the

00:37:51.066 --> 00:37:52.036
color is ignored.

00:37:52.096 --> 00:37:54.386
You can make the starting image

00:37:54.386 --> 00:37:55.616
any color you like, that's

00:37:55.616 --> 00:37:56.186
ignored.

00:37:56.296 --> 00:37:57.556
It's only the transparency.

00:37:58.316 --> 00:37:59.946
They can be bitmaps or PDFs.

00:38:01.306 --> 00:38:02.716
And here's an example from the

00:38:02.716 --> 00:38:04.646
OS of the speaker volume image.

00:38:05.486 --> 00:38:08.046
The original image is black, and

00:38:08.256 --> 00:38:09.626
then it has this partially

00:38:09.626 --> 00:38:11.146
transparent section for the

00:38:11.146 --> 00:38:12.226
larger soundwaves.

00:38:14.196 --> 00:38:16.516
And if we put this image into an

00:38:16.516 --> 00:38:19.866
NSImageView, it's automatically

00:38:19.866 --> 00:38:21.406
given the Secondary Label Color,

00:38:21.406 --> 00:38:24.296
and you can see in light, it's a

00:38:24.826 --> 00:38:26.446
medium gray, and in dark, it's a

00:38:26.446 --> 00:38:27.076
lighter gray.

00:38:27.756 --> 00:38:28.596
And then the partially

00:38:28.596 --> 00:38:30.426
transparent areas have less

00:38:30.426 --> 00:38:33.956
contrast against the background.

00:38:35.426 --> 00:38:36.606
Another advantage of using

00:38:36.606 --> 00:38:37.786
template images is that they

00:38:37.786 --> 00:38:39.136
automatically pick up on the

00:38:39.136 --> 00:38:39.716
button state.

00:38:40.196 --> 00:38:43.746
When a button is disabled, the

00:38:43.746 --> 00:38:45.176
images are dimmer, and that's

00:38:45.176 --> 00:38:47.026
handled for you if you use

00:38:47.026 --> 00:38:47.756
template images.

